\begin_layout Subsection
Parsing the MATPOWER format
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The input 
\family typewriter
.m
\family default
 file contains the base power 
\family typewriter
baseMVA
\family default
 and three matrices: 
\family typewriter
bus
\family default
 (buses: type, load 
\begin_inset Formula $P_d,Q_d$
\end_inset

, shunt 
\begin_inset Formula $G_s,B_s$
\end_inset

, initial voltage), 
\family typewriter
gen
\family default
 (generators: bus, 
\begin_inset Formula $P_g,Q_g$
\end_inset

, specified 
\begin_inset Formula $|V|$
\end_inset

) and 
\family typewriter
branch
\family default
 (branches: 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

, tap ratio 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 and phase shift 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi$
\end_inset

). The parser tolerates comments and whitespace, maps the bus numbering onto contiguous indices, and normalizes all powers to p.u.
\begin_inset space \space{}

\end_inset

by dividing by 
\family typewriter
baseMVA
\family default
. The bus injection is computed as the difference between generation and load, 
\begin_inset Formula $P_i = P_{g,i}-P_{d,i}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_i = Q_{g,i}-Q_{d,i}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Building the Y-bus matrix
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Y-bus is built in a single pass over the branch list according to 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:ybus"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"
tuple "list"

\end_inset

, in the complex natID matrix 
\family typewriter
dense::CmplxMatrix
\family default
; the bus shunt elements are added to the diagonal in a second pass. For the target problem sizes (tens to hundreds of buses) the dense representation is simple and fast enough, and the transition to a sparse structure remains an open direction for larger systems (section
\begin_inset space ~

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:diskusija"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"
tuple "list"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Generating the 
\family typewriter
.dmodl
\family default
 model
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The output is a textual dTwin NL model: the variables (
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_i$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $V_i$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_i^g$
\end_inset

 for PV buses), the parameters and two current balance equations per bus. An example for PQ bus 5 (abbreviated): 
\size small

\end_layout

\begin_layout Verbatim
Y_5_5*V_5*cos(th_5_5+d_5)+... = (P_5*cos(d_5)+Q_5*sin(d_5))/V_5
\end_layout

\begin_layout Verbatim
Y_5_5*V_5*sin(th_5_5+d_5)+... = (P_5*sin(d_5)-Q_5*cos(d_5))/V_5
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
noindent
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (the actual model uses UTF-8 symbols: 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 instead of 
\family typewriter
th
\family default
, 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta$
\end_inset

 instead of 
\family typewriter
d
\family default
). Numeric constants are printed with full double precision, so that the conversion does not introduce any loss of accuracy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Multithreading and the graphical interface
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The conversion runs in a separate worker thread (
\family typewriter
std::thread
\family default
), so the GUI stays responsive even while processing large networks. The worker thread periodically reports progress to the main (GUI) thread via 
\family typewriter
gui::thread::asyncExecInMainThread
\family default
, where the progress indicator and the status message are updated — fulfilling the requirement of real-time progress reporting on another thread. The output model is written through 
\family typewriter
std::ofstream
\family default
, and the content is additionally stored into the output archive (
\family typewriter
put()
\family default
), so it is also accessible from within the dTwin environment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Building and delivery
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The project is built with CMake (C++20) on Linux, macOS and Windows; the accompanying 
\family typewriter
Makefile
\family default
 automatically fetches the dependencies (natID and dTwin as git submodules, plus the precompiled natID libraries for the matching platform), so 
\family typewriter
make
\family default
 works even after a plain 
\family typewriter
git clone
\family default
. The result is a dynamic library (
\family typewriter
cbpf.dll
\family default
/
\family typewriter
.dylib
\family default
/
\family typewriter
.so
\family default
) which is copied into 
\family typewriter
$HOME/ba.natID/plugins
\family default
 and loaded through the 
\series bold
Model 
\begin_inset Formula $\rightarrow$
\end_inset

 Import
\series default
 menu.
\end_layout

